Package jbt.model.task.composite

Class Summary
ModelComposite A ModelComposite task is a task with several children, whose evaluation depends on the evaluation of its children.
ModelDynamicPriorityList This class represents a task with one or more children, only one being evaluated.
ModelParallel ModelParallel is a task that runs all its children simultaneously.
ModelRandomSelector A ModelRandomSelector is a task that behaves just like a ModelSelector, but which walk through its children in a random order.
ModelRandomSequence A ModelRandomSequence is a task that behaves just like a ModelSequence, but which walk through its children in a random order.
ModelSelector This class represents a task with one or more children, which are run sequentially.
ModelSequence A ModeSequence is a task with one or more children which are evaluated sequentially.
ModelStaticPriorityList This class represents a task with one or more children, only one being evaluated.
 

Enum Summary
ModelParallel.ParallelPolicy Enum defining the different policies for a parallel task (ModelParallel): ModelParallel.ParallelPolicy.SEQUENCE_POLICY: means the parallel behaves like a sequence task, that is, it fails as soon as one of its children fail, and it only succeed if all of its children succeed.
